Description: SSB_BPT4 - Also known as ssb. Experimental evidence at protein level: Swiss-Prot protein existence level 1. Single-stranded DNA-binding protein that participates in viral DNA replication, recombination, and repair (Probable). Coats the lagging-strand ssDNA as the replication fork advances (PubMed:9079662). Stimulates the activities of viral DNA polymerase and DnaB-like SF4 replicative helicase, probably via its interaction with the helicase assembly factor (PubMed:14871889). Together with DnaB-like SF4 replicative helicase and the helicase assembly factor, promotes pairing of two homologous DNA molecules containing complementary single- stranded regions and mediates homologous DNA strand exchange (PubMed:11459967). Promotes also the formation of joint molecules (PubMed:9079662). mRNA specific autogenous translational repressor (PubMed:15507125). From Enterobacteria phage T4 (Bacteriophage T4).
β-lactamase; bla; confers resistance to ampicillin, carbenicillin, and related antibiotics
transcription terminator for bacteriophage T7 RNA polymerase
bidirectional E. coli tonB-P14 transcription terminator
LacZα fragment of β-galactosidase; lacZ fragment
